description: For sale in our Atlanta showroom is a classic 1966 Ford Mustang. This A-code pony is a beauty and ready to cruise on down to the drive-in or next show! Powering this 66 Ford Mustang for sale is a straight six.  This Ford engine has plenty of pep in its step, with a snappy throttle, and a subtle exhaust from its factory style exhaust. Backing the reliable six is a 3-speed automatic transmission. Add in disc brakes, and power steering, and you have yourself one fun and easy driving Mustang for sale. The power is thrown to the pavement with ease.  At a glance, it's easy to see that this Mustang is vintage in pedigree. This pretty pony is adorned with a beautiful blue paint. This driver quality stallion has a nostalgic look that's a real blast from the past! With just the right amount of chrome and polished goodies, you can see how the 60s transformed from big bumpers and tail fins, to sharp lines and pure presence. The interior is no different, with a deluxe pony vinyl interior. The sporty buckets up front straddle the shifter and console nicely, while the bench out back begs you to have some friends tag along. Everyone understands why the Mustang was such a popular seller and the car to beat. Options on this 1966 Ford Mustang coupe for sale, include: A/C, AM radio, power brakes, power steering, seat belts, vinyl interior, and radial tires. Whether you're looking for a cruiser, a grocery get'r, or you're simply a Ford enthusiast who love originality, this '66 Mustang for sale is for you! To view the car in greater detail, including 100+ HD photos and HD video, please visit www.gatewayclassiccars.com. description: For sale in our Detroit showroom is a 1966 Ford Mustang Convertible. First introduced late in 1964, the Ford Mustang was similar to the Falcon, but with a redesigned and sporty exterior, and some muscle under the hood. Offered in three different body styles, the convertible Mustang is especially desirable, with coupe and fastback models being offered as well. With a 200 CID I6 engine under the hood, an eye-catching paint job, and a manual convertible top, this Mustang will surely get you plenty of attention out on the open road, or at your local classic car show! This 1966 Mustang is in beautiful condition inside and out as you look at this classic there is no doubt it has been well maintained and while maintaining most of its originality has had several upgrades under the hood to keep it running and looking better including a professional engine rebuild just 2,000 miles ago. Other options on this fantastic Ford include: AM radio, manual convertible top, seat belts, vinyl interior, and radial white wall tires on original wheels with hub caps. Opening the door, you'll find a great black vinyl interior consisting of front bucket seats, and a bench in the rear, so you can take the entire family for a cruise, and look good doing it! With an eye-catching exterior, a convertible top, and a rebuilt engine, this classic Pony car is the beginning of a great generation of American classics, so don't miss out on this chance to own a piece of history! To view this car in greater detail, including HD photos and video, please visit our website at www.GatewayClassic Cars.com, or call (313)-982-3100 for more information.

description: The 1965 Ford Mustang is a timeless classic.  So when you can get this icon looking completely vintage on the outside, but with an upgraded A/C interior and more powerful V8 under the hood, it's the best of everything in one affordable coupe.

A Mustang all dressed in gloss black certainly makes you the dark horse wherever you arrive.  But it takes more than luster to create the desire you see here. Bodywork is well done, creases are crisp, and everything lines up nicely to remind us all why we love this icon.  Plus, the bumpers, badging, and trim are all straight and complete, which is why this overall package is so impressive.   You can tell there have been some nice investments in retaining the stock appearance, right down to the stylized wheel covers.

But inside the upgrades are a bit more obvious.  Nothing goes better with a black exterior than a red interior, and so when the outside was switched to the dark hue, the inside got a sinisterly aggressive color makeover.  So while the red seat covers look stock, and they have a feeling of quality to let you know that they are much younger than '65.  And the carpeting and door panels match its vibrancy.  You get great factory items like heat/defrost sliders and a center console.  Plus, there are nice upgrades like the Grant sports steering wheel and an AM/FM/CD stereo with aux hookup for modern music players.

Under the hood is the legendary 289 cubic-inch V8, and it has been upgraded for both style and substance.  Radiating from the dark engine bay are great elements like the shiny air topper and freshly painted blue valve covers.  Plus, the V8's performance has been enhanced with a Holley four-barrel carburetor, Edelbrock intake, newer radiator, and long tube headers that feed a rumbling dual exhaust.  On the road, the three-speed automatic transmission, power steering, and front disc brakes come together to make sure that this enhanced V8 is one pony that you can easily corral.

You're looking at a two-owner American icon that's been so well cared for you even get the owner's manual.  A Mustang that's turnkey with all the right vintage looks and all the right upgrades is irresistible.  So if you want to make it yours, hurry up and call today!

description: is available in our Fairfield, CA showroom and any inquiries may be directed to us at

New to our Fairfield showroom is this beautifully restored 1965 Ford Mustang 2 Door Coupe with red exterior paint and a black interior. It is a Factory "A" code muscle car it has a 289 CI V-8 engine under the hood with a 4-speed manual transmission, 380 gears, a Posi rear end and traction bars. It also has high performance cam roller rocker lifters, port matched heads and intake manifolds, an Edelbrock aluminum intake manifold, a Holley 650 double pumper carb, a Flowmaster dual exhaust and too many other upgrades to list.

This 1965 Ford Mustang was restored back in 1995 to very high standards and it has only been driven approximately 1500 miles since that time. While it does show some slight signs of aging, this one is incredibly impressive up close and it is an outstanding everyday driver. With great power/torque, a sweet growl from the engine and very nice traction, it is simply a pleasure to drive around the Bay Area in.

Additionally, this ’65 Mustang Coupe is a lifetime California classic that has both the black and yellow plates included in the sale. It also has Centerline aluminum wheels with brand new tires, the original factory AM/FM radio and a completely clean original dash with no cutouts for optional upgrades. This is simply a very well preserved classic that delivers exceptional performance.

Overall, this 1965 Ford Mustang is in phenomenal shape and it drives like it just pulled out of the factory showroom. With all the performance upgrades and such a clean look, this one is an absolute steal at the current asking price. It’s simply too nice to last for long at this price.
